{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a public inquiry into unfair business practices during the pandemic",
        "additional_details": "We believe many people have been victims of unfair business practices in recent years, and that regulatory bodies and ombudsmen (FCA, SFO, F/O, BBRS, TS, CAB and Legal Ombudsman) have not been able to prevent these or provide adequate redress.\r\n\r\nPeople are losing their livelihoods and in some cases their lives & perfectly good businesses are failing because individuals and businesses are not adequately protected.\r\n\r\nA public inquiry could identify unfair practices, and ensure redress is available.",
        "background": "We believe many businesses, families and individuals have been unfairly treated by lenders, lawyers & other businesses during the pandemic. The Government should launch a public inquiry to investigate evidence of unfair business practices during the pandemic, including bullying & harassment.",
